}{\plain \fs24 \b 2. AT Friedrich Nietzsche\par
}{\plain \fs24 \tab (1) The Nietzsche evidence is absolutely unwarranted. If you don{\u8217\'92}t have a clear warrant \softline
on your flow from the NC, don{\u8217\'92}t vote on the argument since it{\u8217\'92}s not fair to expect me to respond \softline
to arguments that aren{\u8217\'92}t clearly articulated. If you{\u8217\'92}re not sure about warranting, read Nietzsche \softline
after the round{\u8211\'96}it{\u8217\'92}s just a string of fancy-sounding descriptive assertions.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \tab (2) Nietzsche just gives a genealogical account of where moral concepts come from. The \softline
fact that these concepts arose in a particular way doesn{\u8217\'92}t determine the validity of claims about \softline
ethics. All concepts are capable of being twisted to serve self-interested goals; that doesn{\u8217\'92}t make \softline
them empty.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
